{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, we find that hypernetworks with the same low value of δ (2) can display very different values of the intra-order hyperedge overlap T ð2Þ.",
    "This is an indication of the independence of the two metrics δ (2) and T ð2Þ in sparse networks.",
    "E.g., for δ (2) = 0.2 × 10 -4 (see vertical dashed line), we observe that the intra-order hyperedge overlap T ð2Þ of realworld systems can vary from values close to 0 to values as large as 0.8.",
    "Similar conclusions can be drawn from the inset in Fig. 1d, where we report the average generalized degree hk ð2Þ i =",
    "i =N and the intraorder hyperedge overlap T ð2Þ for each of the hypernetworks."
  ]
}